Package ch.colabproject.colab.api.model.document

Class AbstractResource

  • java.lang.Object
    • ch.colabproject.colab.api.model.document.AbstractResource
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ColabEntity, StickyNoteSourceable, WithPermission, WithTrackingData, WithWebsocketChannels, ch.colabproject.colab.generator.model.interfaces.WithId, ch.colabproject.colab.generator.model.interfaces.WithJsonDiscriminator, Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Resource, ResourceRef
    @Entity
public abstract class AbstractResource
extends Object
implements ColabEntity, WithWebsocketChannels, StickyNoteSourceable
    A resource is a document provided to help the users to fulfill their goals.

    An abstract resource is either a resource directly representing a document or a reference to another abstract resource.

    An abstract resource can be owned either by a card type / card type reference, or by a card by to a card content.

    Author:
    sandra
